How people think and act in different places affects the way they make agreements. We should not make simple statements about whole groups of people. For example, we should not say "all Russians act this way" or "all Japanese act that way." It is better to learn how people's ways of thinking affect talks between groups.

When we meet people from other places, we often compare them to what we know. To understand others better, we can study their history and learn about what they believe. We should not try to change their ways, but accept them. This is very important when making agreements, especially if we are the weaker side. When we go to another place to talk, showing respect for their ways helps make agreements possible.

Different groups have different ways of doing things, even in the same country. Companies often have their own special ways. Some want workers to stay late, while others let workers leave earlier. You can see how companies are different in how people dress, how they talk to each other, and who they hire. Some companies want workers to help poor people, while others only give money to special groups. Even companies in America can be very different from each other.

What people think is important tells us why they act certain ways. In some places, people think it is very important not to shame others or to keep peace in the group. In these places, someone talking for their company will not shame their leaders to win. In other places, people think it is good to push hard for what they want. Before starting talks, it is good to know these things. But it is also helpful to learn about the person you will talk with.

In the Bible, it is written that only a foolish person says there is no God. Two important Christian thinkers, Anselm and Thomas Aquinas, wrote about why they believe God exists. Both men tried to prove that the God of the Bible is real. To compare their ideas fairly, we must focus on their specific understanding of God. While both men made good points, I think neither one fully explains why we should believe in God.

Let us first look at what Anselm said. Anselm believed that faith helps us understand God. He said that because we can think about God in our minds, God must be real. He thought we could find proof of God by looking inside ourselves. Anselm said we do not need outside proof to know God exists. We only need to think about what we already know in our hearts. In the Christian faith, believing without seeing proof is called faith.

Thomas Aquinas had different ideas. He thought we could prove God exists through careful thinking and by looking at the world around us. This way of proving God would help spread Christianity because people would not need faith first. They would only need to follow clear thinking. Aquinas gave five different reasons to prove God exists. He talked about how things change, how everything has a cause, why things exist, why some things are better than others, and why the world works in an orderly way. His ideas are like looking at a puzzle with one piece missing. Even without seeing the missing piece, you can know its shape and know it exists by looking at the empty space and the pieces around it.

Writers often try to make readers feel certain ways about important things in their stories. F. Scott Fitzgerald does this well in his book The Great Gatsby. He puts words together in special ways to create feelings. He also uses colors to mean special things.

In the book, Fitzgerald gives special meaning to colors like gold, green, white, gray, red, and pink. He is very careful about how he uses white and gray colors to show readers something important.

When Fitzgerald uses white and gray, he wants to show things that are all the same. White often means clean and rich, while gray shows things that are old or less bright. At the start of the book, he shows this by having many people wear white clothes. Daisy and Jordan are always "in white." Nick wears "white" clothes to Gatsby's party. Tom has on a "white shirt" when he meets Myrtle. The only time people wear different colors is at Gatsby's big party.

Fitzgerald also uses white and gray to show regular, everyday things. The city buildings are "white." Names of party guests become "gray" in Nick's memory. Regular people are often shown as white or gray too. The roads have "gray cars," and there are "gray" areas where poor people live.

Later in the story, Fitzgerald uses these colors to show how some things are not special anymore. When he shows Daisy "dressed in white" in a "white car," it helps readers see her differently. She becomes less special and more like everything else. This helps show how Gatsby's dream about her might not be as wonderful as he thinks.

San Diego County grows many foods because of its warm, sunny weather. Farmers grow tomatoes, oranges, green vegetables, and many other foods. They also get honey from bees, and eggs and milk from farm animals.

Many people in San Diego want to buy food grown without chemicals. These "organic" farms often let people visit to learn about farming. People can also walk on the land to see birds and enjoy nature. Farmers can get money from the government to help keep the land good for wild animals while growing food.

Organic farming helps more kinds of plants and animals live on the land because no chemicals are used. But organic farming costs more money because workers must remove bad plants and insects by hand. Small farms also cannot save money the way big farms do. Other things that help wild animals, like planting special plants or moving animals to different fields, also cost more money. This is why farmers often need help to make money while helping nature.

The land in this story is near the town of Potrero in San Diego County. It is 160 acres of wild land next to a national forest. The land has many different kinds of plants and animals. Some of these animals, like special rats and frogs, are in danger of dying out forever.

Native American people lived on this land for many years. Later, in the late 1800s, people came to raise cows and cut wood. Someone got this land from the government long ago and probably used it for cows or wood since then.

I found this land for sale and looked up ways the government could help a farmer. I also found another organic farm nearby to see how they run their farm.

Brothers share a special connection that cannot be broken. This connection includes feelings like love, pride, and anger. Brothers know each other better than anyone else can. When they look at each other, they see themselves. In hard times, this connection becomes very clear, whether it brings good or bad results. These feelings can lead to difficult situations. Brothers must deal with what happens because of their feelings. When they look at each other, they see who they really are, not how others see them. Their true nature shows in what they do and what happens after.

In the story "The Scarlet Ibis," two brothers show us these ideas. They travel through a beautiful area on a journey that cannot succeed. One brother feels very proud while the other feels very sad. At the end, only one brother lives. We see these ideas through the main character and his young brother Doodle, how they act together, and how the older brother tells the story. The older brother's feelings and how he sees the world affect everything he does.

The older brother's actions come from his pride. From the first time he takes Doodle outside until their last walk together, he feels unhappy with his brother. He wanted a brother who could do things with him, like holding his breath, running, jumping, and climbing trees. He wanted someone to race with and sit with high in the pine tree behind their barn. But Doodle could not do these things. He was born with a weak heart, and doctors thought he would die. Even if he lived, he could never run or play hard games. This made the older brother very sad. His dreams about having a normal brother were gone. He was so upset that he even thought about killing baby Doodle with a pillow. But when Doodle smiled at him, the older brother's anger went away. This small act gave him hope. It shows that deep down, he loved his little brother.

The human brain is an amazing system that processes information in complex ways. As humans made new tools through history, they found different ways to explain how the brain works. First, they said it was like a writing tablet, then like paper, then like a book, and now like a computer. But we must remember that these comparisons are not perfect and can sometimes lead to wrong ideas.

The brain first gets information from our senses - touch, heat, sound, and light. These feelings become signals that the brain can use. The brain then changes these signals in different ways. For example, when you look at a black box on a white background, your brain first sees simple things like color and shape. Then your brain puts these simple pieces together to help you quickly know that you are looking at a box.

The brain decides which information is important to think about. For instance, when you look at grass, your brain sees all the small pieces but does not make you notice each one. However, you might hear someone say your name even in a loud room full of people talking.

The brain must store information to use it. There are different kinds of memory. Some memories last only a few seconds, while others can last for many years. When you learn something new, your brain first changes it into a form it can save. For example, when you learn a new word, you might remember what it looks like, how it sounds, or what it means. Scientists think short memories stay in the brain as electrical signals, while long memories are kept in special proteins.

Scientists have different ideas about how the brain organizes what we know. One idea says that the brain connects related things together, like linking the word "chair" to "table" because they are both furniture. These connections help us remember and understand things better.

In 2007, the United States faced a severe money crisis. Many people lost their jobs, house prices fell sharply, and major companies failed. These problems continue today, so we must ask: what caused this, and how can we prevent it?

The crisis began because of poor choices by government leaders. Banks were pushed to give home loans to people who could not pay them back. Two big government-supported companies, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, bought these risky loans and sold them to others. When people could not pay their loans, banks lost money. This problem spread through the whole economy.

The trouble started in 1999 when President Clinton wanted to win more public support. His government made it easier for people to get home loans. A New York Times writer, Steven Holmes, warned about this in 1999. He wrote that Fannie Mae was being pushed to give more loans to people with low and middle incomes. Holmes correctly predicted that this could lead to serious problems if the economy turned bad.

Several things made the situation worse. Banks created new, complex ways to handle home loans. They mixed these loans together and sold them to other companies. This meant that when house prices fell, it hurt many parts of the economy.

When house prices dropped, many banks and investment companies lost huge amounts of money. The five largest U.S. investment banks owed $4.1 trillion in 2007. Two of these banks were sold for very low prices, one failed completely, and two others had to change how they operated. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac owed $5 trillion and had to be taken over by the government in 2008.

Let's talk about telling stories. Writers often want to give too much information at once. This can make readers stop reading or feel tired. Even experienced writers sometimes make this mistake.

It is better not to give too much information all at once.

Most writers know they should show things instead of just telling them. But sometimes we write long parts where nothing happens, or we try to tell too many things at the same time. We might think we need to explain everything about the past before we can tell the real story. Or we might want to tell every small detail about our characters' lives.

Telling too much means explaining things in a simple way, without showing action. In movies, this happens when one person tells another person a lot of information all at once. In books, the writer does this directly to the reader.

Here is an example. Think about a story where a woman meets someone she loves. They get married in a big wedding. Then her husband is killed while she watches. If this takes only two pages, and they only speak four times, something is wrong. The writer should show us more about the husband. We should see how he acts and talks, and how much he loves his wife. We should see how the wife's life becomes better because of him. This helps readers care about what happens. It also helps us understand the wife better: what she likes about him, how close they were, and what she hopes for in life.

The simple story "They met, they married, he died" needs more details to make it real.

As a writer, you must add these important details. Sometimes you want to move quickly past parts of the story. For example, you might have a new person in your story who used to fly planes, now works at night at a gas station, was married two times, has no children, likes to fish, wants to own the gas station, and ate eggs for breakfast. But you should not tell all of this at once.

I watched two news shows from Columbus, Ohio. The first one was on NBC 4 on the morning of August 13, 2011. The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio who had hurt his wife with a knife. The man's name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture from the police. The story was short because it was still new. They only told us that he had hurt his wife many times with the knife and that police had caught him. I think they used the right amount of time for this story.

The second story was about a young man named Travis Buyers, who was 18 years old. Someone shot him in the Sharon Woods area, and he was very badly hurt. Police had not caught anyone yet. Special police teams were looking into what happened. I think this story was too short, maybe because it happened in an area where many black people live. I have seen for many years that when bad things happen to people who are not white, the news does not tell much about it. But when something bad happens to white people, the news talks about it a lot.

They then told about a hole made by a gun in a medical flying machine. They said someone shot it with a small gun. People who help solve crimes are offering money if someone can help find who did it.

The weather news was next. They said it would rain later, and it would not be too hot. They kept this part short so people would keep watching.

They also told about someone taking money from a store on Clime Road. They spent a lot of time talking about how the person who did it was black. They told how tall he was and what clothes he was wearing.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez who sold bad things from Texas to Ohio. They said he must stay in prison for 300 months, which is the same as 25 years. They said he was Hispanic, which did not seem important to the story.

Let me explain what an ETF is and how it works. An ETF (Exchange Traded Fund) is a type of investment that follows a group of companies or products. It works like a regular stock that you can buy and sell during the trading day.

When you buy an ETF, you are buying a small part of many different companies at once. This helps reduce your risk because your money is spread across many businesses. You can buy just one share, or you can buy many shares. You can also sell ETF shares quickly if you need to.

ETFs usually cost less money to own than other types of investments like mutual funds. However, you do have to pay a small fee each time you buy or sell ETF shares, just like when you trade regular stocks.

In this study, we looked at an ETF called IHF to see if it was better to own the ETF or to buy shares of the ten biggest companies in the ETF separately. These ten companies make up about 64% of the entire ETF.

When we studied the numbers, we found something interesting. If you owned just these ten companies in the same amounts as they appear in the ETF, you could make about 16% more money than owning the ETF itself. The investment would also be less risky.

To make sure these findings were real and not just by chance, we needed to look at how much these investments changed in value over time. We did this by studying how much each stock's price moved up and down, and compared this to the ETF's movements.

Looking at the numbers in Figure 17, we saw that fewer people sent in their travel records during the third month. This made us worry. We are not sure why this happened.

When winter comes to our area, fewer people ride bikes or walk to school. This could explain some of the drop. December is also when the school term ends. Everyone is busy finishing work and giving grades. People might have forgotten to write down how they traveled. December is also holiday time, when students and teachers do not need to come to school for a month. School starts again in late January, which might explain why few people sent in records that month. But this does not explain why February's numbers were so low.

Any project like this might start with great interest that later goes down. To fight this drop, we made a special week in March called "Carpool Challenge Week." This helped increase the number of records sent in that month. One of our big problems was keeping people interested when they naturally become less involved, especially during school breaks.

Another problem is that people like driving their own cars. They enjoy being free to go where they want, when they want. This is a big part of how we live. So, we needed to give people reasons to try other ways to travel. We gave out many prizes like gift cards for restaurants, coffee shops, book stores, and other places. We wonder if bigger prizes, like a new bike or electric car, would have made more people join. If we had started with small prizes and then offered bigger ones later, like bikes in December and a car in January, more people might have stayed interested in the project.

I studied some early films at the Library of Congress. I looked at fifteen special films made by Thomas Edison between 1895 and 1901. These were called "trick films" because they used special ways of joining film pieces to create magic-like effects.

Most of these early films followed simple rules. They were filmed inside on a stage, like a theater. The camera always stayed in one place, pointing straight at the stage. The films showed the whole stage or most of it, but never came close to the actors' faces. Each film was usually just one scene.

However, some films made in the early 1900s started to break these rules. They began using more than one scene in a single film.

One thing all these trick films shared was that they were filmed on an inside stage, like you would see in a theater. The camera never moved to follow the people or things in the film. This way of filming came from theater shows and magic acts. Because of this, the people in these films usually only moved from left to right on the stage. They did not walk toward or away from the camera. For example, in the film "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel" (1900), the actors come in from the right side and move back and forth across the stage.

The way these films were made meant that everything was shown from far away or middle distance. The camera never showed close-up views of faces or things. This was like watching a theater show, where you see everything happening on the whole stage at once.

Most early trick films were very short, usually less than one minute long. They showed simple magic tricks, like people appearing and disappearing. They did not tell long stories. Even though these films looked like one continuous scene, they were actually made by joining several pieces of film together carefully. You can see this in "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots" (1895) if you look very carefully at the moment when her head appears to be cut off.

The old writing style called "Gothic" combines both old and new ideas in interesting ways. Writers who used this style were both praised and criticized for their work. The first Gothic story, "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole, mixed old theater ideas with new ways of writing about people and nature.

The Gothic style borrowed many ideas from the Middle Ages, including building styles and old stories. When "The Castle of Otranto" was written, the word "gothic" was used to describe many different things from the past. Many people thought these old ways were not as good as new ones. However, the Gothic style stayed popular because it mixed old theater ideas with new ways of showing how people think and feel.

One important idea in Gothic stories is the code of honor called "chivalry." This comes from the Middle Ages, when knights were trained to be brave and good. Writers like Walpole thought their own time needed more of these good qualities. They wrote about the past to try to make their present time better.

When Walpole wrote his story, his country was having political problems. He may have thought people in his time were not as good or honest as people in the past. We can see this in his story through characters like Frederic. Before we meet Frederic in the story, we learn he is a brave and suffering prince who people think died fighting enemies. This shows the old ideas of what a good knight should be, though Walpole makes these qualities bigger than life to make his point.

Moving goods from start to end is called supply chain management. It begins when a customer orders something and includes getting raw materials, making the product, and sending it to the customer. Keith Oliver, who helped businesses work better, first used this term in 1982. He explained how to plan and control the movement of goods to make customers happy quickly and well.

There are six main parts to moving goods: making things, getting supplies, keeping products ready, choosing where to work, moving things around, and sharing information. Business leaders use these six parts to serve customers well.

Making things is the first and most important part. Leaders must know what to make and how many to make. They look at what people want to buy to make these choices. They also need to pick the best place to make things, thinking about how many they can make and how good they will be.

After picking where to make things, leaders must plan when workers will work and how to keep machines running well. Every small part of making things must be planned carefully. If not, it can cost much money and time later. For example, stores like Walmart and Target have clear plans for everything - from what workers wear to how trucks bring things to the store.

Getting supplies is the second main part. Leaders must choose what each workplace will do best and what work to give to other companies. Sometimes, different places make different parts of one thing. Leaders may ask other companies to help make things if it helps them work faster and save money while still making good products.

Books from the Victorian time often described small details of life among rich people. However, two famous books, "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights," were different. These stories used mystery and strange events to help readers better understand the characters' feelings and actions.

In "Oliver Twist," we often see these strange events through dreams or dream-like moments. For example, when Oliver is shot, he experiences the event again later in his mind:

"He thought he was walking with Sikes and Crackit. He could hear their angry voices clearly. Then he heard guns fire and people shouting. Lights flashed before his eyes. Everything was loud and confusing. Someone he could not see pulled him away quickly. Through all these quick pictures in his mind, he felt pain that would not go away."

These dream-like moments show us what is happening inside Oliver's mind. When he remembers being shot, we see how little control he had over what happened to him. He feels lost and afraid. The pain stays with him, mixing with his fear. We can see that Oliver feels helpless, unable to fight against what is happening to him. It seems that Fagin, the bad man who controls him, has started to break Oliver's spirit. Otherwise, Oliver might have tried harder to save himself.

Time itself seems strange to Oliver: "The day went by - what day? There was no day; it came and went too fast - and night came again. The night felt so long because it was so quiet, but the hours passed too quickly."

I worked helping young students after school two years ago. I helped them with their studies, but I was best at teaching reading and writing in English. A teacher asked me to help a young boy named Adrian, who was in grade three or four. He had trouble reading. I noticed something strange about how he read. He could say some letters well, but others he could not say at all. Adrian was from a Latino family, but he spoke English very well.

One day, while watching some students who stayed behind from a school trip, I met Adrian's mother. She only spoke Spanish and no English. Even with my poor Spanish, we could talk a little. Then I understood the problem: Adrian could read, but he did not know the English letters well.

I share this story to talk about problems with language in our schools, especially in California. Sometimes these problems are hard to see. Even when a child speaks English well, reading can be very hard. We all know this is a problem, so what should we do? For Adrian, the answer was simple: he needed help learning English letters and their sounds. But for children who do not speak much English, the answer is not so simple. We have many ways to help: teaching in two languages, putting students in English-only classes, having special teachers, or English learning classes. No single way will fix everything. We need to use all of these ways together!

Teaching in two languages is very good for all students, not just those who speak Spanish first. Studies show that students in two-language programs do better in school than other students. Some people think this wastes money and only helps a few students. This is wrong. If we teach this way in all classes, every student would learn better. We do not need all teachers to speak two languages. That would be too hard to do. But we can have special helpers who speak both languages in our schools.

As children, we learn about powers greater than ourselves. Some learn at church, others at different places of worship, and some look inside themselves for answers. Many accept the religious beliefs their parents teach them. Others refuse to believe in anything they cannot see or touch. People may change what they believe as they grow. No matter what path we choose, we all try to understand life's big questions in our own way. We look for light to guide us through dark times.

"A red bird," my father told me when I asked about his favorite bird. We sat on our front porch, listening to rain hit the metal roof while we smoked. Water poured from the roof edges, falling on the plants below. He looked into the distance, as if thinking of something far away. He had become very thin, and his clothes hung loose on his body. His hair was thinner than I remembered. He kept looking at the rain, not at me. I felt scared and alone. I could not tell him how much I would miss him because speaking about it would make it too real. I moved closer and hugged him. Then I sat next to him, watching the rain fall in the growing darkness.

My father died in December that year, just after my birthday. The medical treatments did not stop his pain, they only kept him alive longer. I could not understand why. I wondered how a good power could let this happen. At night, I stopped praying. I thought if there was a God, He no longer heard me.

I did not want to watch my father die, so I stayed away. I wanted to remember how he lived, not how he left us. I knew him better than anyone, and I knew he would not want me to watch him die. I stayed in bed for three days, waiting to hear the news.

No one called to tell me when he died.

John Taylor was an early supporter of the Republican way of thinking in America. He worked mainly as a farmer, and this job, along with his short time in government, made him known for speaking strongly about personal freedom and how the government should work. His love of farming shaped most of his ideas about government. He tried to protect farming because he thought it was the best kind of work, and this affected his views on power, law, and courts.

Taylor thought the United States had a special chance to make a perfect system. This was because the new country did not have old rules that would get in the way of making a government run by the people. He believed strongly that people have basic rights that cannot be taken away. He said these rights work together - if you lose one right, you lose value in all of them. He thought the government should not be able to touch these rights. Some people said that without rules, strong and clever but bad people would win, but Taylor said this should not happen in a good society.

To make this good society, Taylor said we need a government that understands both the good and bad in people. He had strong beliefs about right and wrong. He said that since people run the government, the good and bad in government comes from people. He thought good rules were ones that protected what people owned, helped farming grow, and stopped big business from having too much power. He believed that even if the people running the government were thinking about themselves, good rules would make things fair. He knew people always think about themselves first, but said this only becomes bad when some groups live by taking from others. A good government was needed to control people's bad side, but it needed to be watched carefully.

Taylor, like other Republicans at that time, wanted people to follow the Constitution exactly as it was written. He wanted a small federal government that could only do what the Constitution clearly said it could do. He knew a big federal government would cost too much money and might become too controlling. But he also thought just reading the words simply could be dangerous, and said we need to think about what the writers meant. He thought the Declaration of Independence was even more important than the Constitution because it showed that the states should be free to rule themselves.

I looked down at the toilet, my mind trying to understand what I saw. I watched without feeling, like someone studying something far away. Thoughts came and went quickly. My mind felt clear, as if I was only seeing, not thinking.

Once, an artist told me to buy a book called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." Since I was six, I wanted to learn to draw. The book teaches everything about drawing, from how to hold a pencil to how the brain sees lines. One lesson teaches you to put a frame around what you want to draw. This makes a complex picture simpler. For example, a bowl of fruit in a kitchen becomes just a bowl on a flat surface.

As I stood there looking at the toilet, I could not imagine such a frame. I was too surprised by what I saw. Artists like Picasso had his blue pictures, and Monet loved to paint green gardens. If I were an artist, this would be my brown period.

My fingers touched the handle, and my hand moved through the air. The water moved smoothly and clearly. Small pieces broke away and disappeared. Moving more quickly the second time, my hand hit the handle again. The brown mass stayed at the bottom of the toilet, not moving.

I stood there in my work clothes, green tie tight around my neck, holding a mop. I looked at what someone had left for the workers who clean the bathrooms at Rite Aid. After trying to flush several more times, I reached for the toilet paper. I wrapped my hand in paper until it looked like a thick glove. Standing straight, then bending down, my hand went slowly into the bowl, like reaching into an oven for food.

Young people are dying while driving cars. Several things work together to make driving very dangerous for the youngest drivers in America. Health experts say one part of the problem is that young minds are not ready for the dangers of driving. Having little experience is another big problem. This lack of experience leads to more deadly crashes, cars turning over, driving too fast, and going off the road.

Young drivers have more problems when they drive with their friends, which they often do. A study in Southern California showed that there is a clear link between how old passengers are and how many crashes happen.

California and other states have tried to make young drivers safer. They give special licenses that only let young people drive at certain times and do not let them drive with other young people in the car.

But these special licenses are only a short-term answer. The real problem is that the youngest drivers, as a group, cannot handle the dangers and duties of driving well enough. One expert who studies human behavior thinks even age 18 is too young to drive. He found that people under age 20 often want to do dangerous things just for fun. Because of this, it makes sense to wait to let people drive until they are less likely to take such risks.

If we keep giving driver's licenses to young people, we will keep seeing deadly crashes. The problem will get worse in coming years as more young people become old enough to drive.

The answer could be simple. Schools could still teach driving, but no one under 18 could drive a car. New drivers would still need to learn and practice with an adult for a set time before getting a full license. Since this problem affects all states, making one law for the whole country would be a good way to protect young people everywhere.

This idea is not new, but it could save many lives.

This paper looks at three parts of a brain condition that affects how people process sound. The condition is called Central Auditory Processing Disorder, or CAPD for short.

First, I will explain what CAPD is. People with CAPD can hear sounds normally, but their brains cannot process these sounds correctly. For example, they may have trouble understanding words when there is noise in the room. Their ears work fine, but their brains have difficulty making sense of what they hear.

Second, I will describe how doctors find out if someone has CAPD. There are certain signs that may show someone has this condition. For instance, a person might have trouble telling where a sound is coming from, or understanding when someone is joking by their tone of voice.

Third, I will share ways teachers can help students with CAPD in regular classrooms. This is important because many students with CAPD study in normal school settings.

CAPD was first noticed by doctors in the 1950s. They saw it while studying children who had trouble communicating. Since then, doctors have created different tests to check for CAPD. These tests often ask people to listen to different sounds or words at the same time and then tell them apart.

To check if someone has CAPD, doctors watch how a person listens and responds to different sounds. They may also ask questions about how the person handles sounds in daily life. At this time, there is no single test that can show for sure if someone has CAPD, and doctors do not know what causes it.

I want to work in social services to help children who have been hurt by their families. I also want to help families who are having problems. I can bring important things to this work: being helpful, showing respect, doing what is right, and always trying to learn more to do my job better. These things are important not just for the job, but to me as a person.

I always knew I wanted to help others, but I was not sure how. In school, I saw many people run away from their problems or deal with them in wrong ways. This made me study the science of how people think and act. After finishing school in 2009, I took some time to think about what to do next.

One summer day, I met a young boy at a friend's house. He was there because his parents were hurting him. The next day, he called the police about his parents. I went to help and told the police about my school training. They asked me to talk to the parents. The parents acted worried and said their son was just causing trouble. This made me want to become a social worker to help children with family problems.

I also believe everyone should be treated fairly. Our society says each person is special, but often pushes people to be the same as others. I do not like this. In school, I showed this by looking different from others and standing up for people who were treated badly because they were different. I joined groups that helped people who were treated unfairly. I will keep working to make sure everyone is treated fairly.

This paper looks at two ways to understand sleep problems, especially when people cannot sleep well. One way looks at how the body works and what we get from our parents through our genes. The other way looks at how where we live, our culture, and our place in society affect our sleep.

When someone has trouble sleeping, doctors put it into different groups. The main groups are problems with getting to sleep, problems during sleep, and sleep troubles that come from other health issues. Problems with getting to sleep can mean staying awake when you want to sleep, or feeling too sleepy during the day. Some people even fall asleep suddenly without warning.

The body part that controls sleep is in the brain. Special brain cells help decide when we are awake or asleep. Scientists studied mice to learn how these cells work. They found that certain parts of brain cells, called receptors, are very important for sleep. When these receptors work well, animals can sleep normally. When they do not work well, sleep becomes hard.

If someone gets bad sleep receptors from their parents, they might always have trouble sleeping. This can make life hard. It can cause problems at school or work, especially when doing boring tasks that need attention. People might need medicine to help them sleep if their brain cells do not work right.

Studies with mice help us understand how human sleep works. However, humans are more complex than mice, so we must be careful about what we learn from these studies.

I have been studying at University Park for more than two years now. Moving around this large school area is hard for many students, including me. When I first came here, I lived in East Halls, which is very far from the center of school. Walking from my room in Stuart Hall to my classes in Willard building would take about 25 minutes, especially when the weather was bad. 

An older student told me that not long ago, East Halls stood alone, far from other buildings. Now that empty land has new sports fields and big buildings, including places for food and health care. As our school grows bigger, it gets harder to move from place to place. The best answer to this problem is the bicycle. But just having bikes is not enough. Students need to use them, and the school needs to make roads that are good for bike riders.

A friend who started riding bikes again after many years told me something interesting. He said he did not know why he ever stopped using a bike. He thinks bikes are the best way to move around school. Riding a bike is good for your health and uses very little energy. A simple breakfast can give you enough power to ride 30 miles or more.

I now live away from school, but my home is as far from classes as some school rooms are. Buying a bike was the best choice I made this year. I have class in Thomas building every day, which would take 25 minutes to reach by walking. On my bike, I can get there in 5 minutes if I ride fast. The only problem is that Pollock Road, the shortest way there, can be hard to use sometimes.

Walking is fine, but I do not have enough time for it. Without my bike, I would have to walk everywhere. Walking to Thomas building every day would take 40 more minutes than riding. That means more than two hours every week just for one class. When you think about all my other classes and things I need to do, walking would take too much of my time.

In his book "Brave New World," Aldous Huxley warns us about the dangers of technology and business control. He creates a future world where people care more about the group than themselves. From birth, they are taught to want only quick happiness. The people are like pieces in a game, controlled by powerful leaders who tell them what to think.

Looking at the book through the ideas of Marx, we can see what worried Huxley about how society was changing. He shows how everyone is made to be the same and how people are treated like things to be used.

The story shows how business controls people by keeping them from understanding their true place. People only care about getting things for themselves. In the book, different groups of workers called Delta and Gamma are taught while they sleep to always buy things and enjoy themselves. They cannot think for themselves. The top leaders control everything, but the workers do not know this.

No real friendships exist in this future world. Even the main people in the story are simple, without much personality. Huxley might be saying that technology and business together take away what makes us human. There is no love. Men only talk about how women look, and women speak without shame about their time with different partners.

Each group of people accepts their place without question. They obey completely, thinking they are better than others as long as they keep buying things and following rules. They must stay the same as everyone else in their group.

I studied Islam at my local college four years ago. In class, we often talked about whether Islam was a religion that wanted peace or war. This question is even more important today. Since the attacks of September 11, 2001, I have seen how news groups changed their views about Islam. At first, they were very against it. Now, they are very accepting of it in America. Back in 2001, no one would have thought we could have someone like Barack Obama, who has family members who were Muslim, run for president.

The life story of Muhammad interests me because what I read seems different from what I knew before. I used to think Muhammad made people follow Islam by force after he won battles. But the book shows him as a good man who was not understood by others. It says people came to him on their own to learn his teachings.

I saw that the book tells stories about Muhammad that are very close to stories about Jesus. For example, it talks about how Muhammad made a small amount of food become enough to feed forty men. This is much like what Jesus did. I think the writers wanted to make Muhammad seem like a quiet, holy man. But this makes less of Jesus's real miracles and life.

The book has many stories about people becoming Muslim on their own. But these stories often come from someone who heard it from someone else, who heard it from another person. This makes me doubt if the stories are true.

What bothers me most is how the book tries to show Muhammad as a good, quiet, and wise man. But what we know from history shows he was different. I wonder if Muslims today know the true story of how Muhammad gained his power.

The ideas Jesus taught during his life were quickly changed as Christian thinking grew after his death. Looking at history, we can see Christianity moved further from what Jesus first taught. Today, more people seem to understand this and want change. While some people still hold firmly to old ways of thinking, they may not be enough to stop new ideas.

In the years ahead, Christians will learn more about their history. They will want to know what ideas were added to their religion after Jesus, and what Jesus really meant to teach. This change may take many years, but it will happen. Christian history will turn around and go back toward its beginning. People will remove added teachings one by one, like going back in time. In the end, only Jesus' original message from God will remain.

When this change spreads across America and Europe, many people will want to follow only what Jesus taught. Churches will still be important, but they will be different. As people go back to earlier ways, the many different kinds of Christian groups will become more alike. Instead of having many different beliefs, Christians will share more common ideas.

History shows us that big changes can happen. For example, Rome once killed Christians, but later became Christian itself. America once had slaves, but now has African-American leaders. This coming change in Christianity will be like this. People will look for the first teachings of Jesus, and many different Christian groups will become more alike. To understand Jesus better, people will learn to read his words as having deeper meaning, not just as simple statements.

Let us look at how Christianity began. It started with the Jewish religion. By the time Rome took control of Jerusalem in 63 BCE, Jewish people believed in one God, followed their holy books, and thought God had given them their religion. But Jewish people were divided into different groups: the Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, Zealots, and many regular people who did not belong to any special group.

After reading "The Jungle," I see that people often think only about themselves and want more than they need. This is very clear in the story, especially when we look at the factory owners and leaders.

These business owners only want their companies to grow bigger and make more money. They do not care who gets hurt along the way. In the book, Upton Sinclair describes the factories with their tall smoke stacks sending dark smoke into the sky. This shows how the owners do not care about hurting the air or the land around them. They also do not worry about the dirty water and waste from the many animal areas.

The owners treat their workers very badly. They care more about money than people. Workers must work long hours in dangerous places. The owners can stop giving people work at any time, leaving families with no money to buy food. During this time, there were no laws to protect workers. No one helped these poor people who worked in the factories.

Some groups said they would help the workers, but they often just took the workers' money. The workers could not leave these bad jobs because they had no other choices. They were like slaves, as Sinclair writes. Most were poor people from other countries who were always close to having no food. The factory owners treated them as badly as slave owners once did.

This book shows us that when people only think about getting more money and power, they often hurt others. The factory owners in "The Jungle" show this truth very clearly.

Edgar Allan Poe wrote a poem called "Dream-Land" which he thought was one of his best works. In this poem, he uses the word "Thule" two times. This word comes from old stories about a far-away island north of Britain. Ancient Greeks thought this was the edge of the world they knew.

While the word has old roots, Poe likely got it from more recent writing. He read many German writers, and one of them was Johann Wolfgang von Goethe. Goethe wrote a famous story called "Faust" that came out in two parts - the first in 1808 and the second in 1832, the year he died.

In "Faust," there is a short poem about "The King of Thule." This poem tells of a king whose wife dies after giving him a special cup. After she dies, the king drinks a lot and cries when he thinks of her. He gives everything he owns to his children, except the cup. He then walks to a high cliff, throws the cup into the sea, and dies. The sad king in this story is much like the person in Poe's "Dream-Land."

Poe wrote about Thule in two different works. He used it in "The Pit and the Pendulum" and twice in "Dream-Land." When you read "Dream-Land," you can see how it matches with "The King of Thule." Poe writes about a dark, lonely place where dead friends appear as spirits. The world he describes has no color. This is like the world of Goethe's sad king, who lost his wife and did not want to live anymore.

Poe knew about Goethe's work because Goethe was very famous. Many people were making new versions of his stories when Poe was writing. Also, Poe respected the poet Tennyson, who thought highly of Goethe's work.

Let me explain a legal case about safety in a store in California. 

A woman named Jennifer Palmer fell in a grocery store and hurt her back. She fell because there was spilled applesauce on the floor. Before she fell, two workers told the store manager about the spill. The manager, Paul Martin, did not clean it up because he was eating his dinner. The spill stayed on the floor for thirty minutes before Palmer fell.

The store had other problems with safety. In the same year, five other people had fallen in the store. Palmer wants the store to pay money for her injury. She also wants extra money as punishment because the manager knew about the danger but did nothing.

In California, a person can get extra money if someone hurts them on purpose or acts very badly. The law says the bad actions must show the person knew they could hurt others but did not care. 

Palmer has a good case for extra money because:
- The manager knew about the spill
- He was told twice about it
- He did nothing to clean it up
- Many people had fallen before
- He knew spills could hurt people

A judge will likely let Palmer try to get this extra money because the manager seemed to ignore the safety of his customers.

She felt she needed something in her life. This feeling would not go away. It began when she was 14, as she entered her teenage years. Now at 17, the feeling remained. She knew she wanted a person, not a thing. Yet no boys interested her. Some boys liked her and tried to get her attention, but she felt nothing for them. She often wondered why she was different from other teenage girls. After thinking about this for years, she had some ideas but no clear answers. So she continued to live her life, still wondering about these feelings.

Life at home was usually quiet. Her parents were good people who lived peacefully. They rarely had arguments with each other or with their daughter. The only problems came when she tried to show she could make her own choices. While her parents were quiet people, she was full of life and fun. People liked her because she was both friendly and kind.

But this day was not peaceful. As she walked through the house looking for something to do, she heard her mother cry out from the kitchen. She ran to the kitchen asking, "Mom? Mom, what is wrong?" She found her mother on the floor, clearly hurt. Her mother kept saying "ow" and breathing hard. The daughter went to help her mother. "Please... take me... to the hospital," her mother said with difficulty. "Show me where to hold you," the daughter said. She was glad she had learned how to lift heavy things. She carried her mother to the car, put her in the back seat, and drove to the hospital.

The hospital had strong smells and worried people. But the daughter only thought about helping her mother. She carried her mother inside and called for help. Doctors came quickly. They put her mother on a bed with wheels and took her away for care. The daughter could only wait and worry.

Later, she learned her mother had fallen while trying to reach a flower container from a high shelf.

This research looked at how eating foods common to countries near the Mediterranean Sea might help prevent heart and blood vessel problems. The study focused on foods like fruits, nuts, whole grains, fish, and plant-based proteins. This way of eating uses healthy oils instead of animal fats, and allows drinking small amounts of wine.

Earlier studies showed that people who ate these foods had better health and lived longer. They also found that this eating plan worked better than low-fat diets for losing weight and improving blood test results. However, these studies did not look closely at how this diet might prevent strokes.

The study watched 74,886 women between ages 38 and 63 for twenty years. All were nurses working in eleven different states, and none had heart problems or diabetes when the study began. Six times between 1984 and 2004, the women filled out forms about what they ate. Almost all the women stayed in the study for the full twenty years. 

The researchers checked hospital records and death certificates to confirm when women had heart attacks or strokes. They also looked at other things that affect health, like weight, smoking, exercise, and medicine use.

To get the best picture of how women ate over time, researchers averaged their eating patterns across years. They were careful to consider other things that might affect the results, like age and exercise.

The study found that women who followed the Mediterranean eating plan most closely had fewer heart problems and strokes. During the twenty years, 2,391 women had heart problems, 1,763 had strokes, and 1,077 died from heart disease or stroke. Women who ate the most Mediterranean-style foods had about 29% less risk of these health problems compared to those who ate the least of these foods.

A young actress stands on a street with a sign. The sign suggests that a cruel leader like Hitler now controls Burma, a country in Southeast Asia.

Since 1962, soldiers have ruled Burma, which is also called Myanmar. In 2007, people there began to protest in the streets for the first time in many years. Many Buddhist holy men, wearing orange-colored clothes, led these protests. When more people joined the protests, the soldiers became angry. They attacked the Buddhist places of worship and hurt many people. They also arrested news reporters from other countries. One photographer from Japan was killed just for taking pictures of the protests. While the government said only thirteen people died, a soldier who left the army said thousands were killed.

This kind of cruel control has happened many times in history. Leaders have often tried to stop people who disagree with them. Some rulers even said they were gods to make people follow them.

There are other sad examples from recent times. In China in 1989, students and workers gathered in a large city square to protest against their government. Many were killed. In Africa, in the 1990s, one group of people in Rwanda tried to kill another group, and many died. In the 1940s, Hitler killed millions of Jewish people in Europe.

These terrible things show us that some leaders will do anything to keep power over their people.

Duke Ellington was very important to jazz music because he led his band for many years. While he played piano, his greatest skill was writing music that showed how good each person in his band could play. He created music that let players make up their own parts while also writing exact parts for the whole band to play together. He knew how to make the band sound special in each song. Because he understood how each player sounded alone and with others, he wrote some of the best jazz music ever made.

One of his famous songs is called "Creole Love Call." In this song, he used a singer's voice like another instrument in the band, without using words. This was something new at the time. The song has six main parts:

Part 1: The voice and wind instruments play back and forth. The voice starts smooth and ends rough.
Part 2: A quiet trumpet plays alone, changing the main tune.
Part 3: A high clarinet plays alone, with soft piano in the back.
Part 4: The whole band plays like the first part.
Part 5: The wind instruments play high notes while others play strong beats.
Part 6: Like the first part again, but the voice makes rough sounds like an instrument.
The song ends with the voice running up and down notes, and the trombone makes an unusual ending sound.

In other songs like "Hot and Bothered" and "It Don't Mean a Thing," Ellington kept finding new ways to mix voices and instruments. He would have trumpet players and singers work together to make special sounds. He also wrote great parts for his long-time trombone player, Joe Nanton.

How do living things change over time? What limits the way they can change? In 1917, a scientist named D'Arcy Thompson said that we could not describe living things using math. This is still mostly true today.

Recently, scientists have used math to study how sea animal shells grow and change over many years. Our team studies a type of sea animal called Prunum. We want to learn how these animals' shells change as they grow and how this affects their long-term change over many generations.

We took X-ray pictures of different Prunum shells to measure important parts. We put these measurements into a computer program called CerioShell. This helped us make pictures of possible shell shapes. By studying these shapes and doing tests, we can better understand how these animals changed over a very long time.

A shell is like a tube that goes around in a circle many times. These circles are called whorls. The whorls turn around a center line called the columella. As the shell grows, the whorls can get bigger at different speeds. A line between each whorl is called a suture. The biggest whorl is usually the last one, called the body whorl. All other whorls make up the spire. The top of the spire is called the apex, and the bottom is called the base. The animal comes out through a hole called the aperture.

You can look at shells from different sides: the top, bottom, front, and back. Usually, people look at shells from the front, with the hole facing them and the top pointing up.

To count whorls, look at the shell from the top. Find where the first line between whorls starts. Draw a line to split the shell in two parts. Count the whorls from this line. You can count parts as small as one-quarter of a whorl.

As the animal builds its shell, it makes new openings that move through space. Scientists can follow this path by measuring the center of each opening and how wide and tall it is.

We can draw pictures and use math to show how shells grow. When we understand the math, we can change numbers to see how different shells might look.

The number of babies and young children who die in Indonesia has stayed almost the same for the past ten years. The country is doing well in some areas, like providing clean water. However, it is not doing well enough to reach its goals for making mothers and children healthier by 2015. There are many reasons for this, which show that the whole health system needs to be made stronger.

More births in Indonesia now happen with trained health workers present - about 72 out of 100 births. However, many of these workers are traditional helpers who cannot deal with serious problems during birth. This means many mothers still die from losing too much blood. Also, fewer sick children under five years old are being seen by doctors. We also know that not enough mothers get care after having their babies.

Only 4 out of 100 babies are born by operation, which is too low. In cities, 7 out of 100 babies are born this way, but in rural areas, only 2 out of 100 are. This shows that health care is much better in cities than in rural areas. Also, rich people get much more health care than poor people. The difference is very large - 27 out of 100. Poor people often cannot pay for health care.

Indonesia must decide how to fix these problems. They could make special programs just for mothers and babies, or they could make the whole health system better. Special programs might work faster and be easier to manage. But these programs can cause problems. When a lot of money goes to one health program, other important health services get less money and fewer workers. Also, having many different programs doing the same work wastes time and money. Workers must fill out too many forms and papers to get supplies and money.

Over the past hundred years, popular music has grown to include many different types. There are now so many kinds of music that it is hard to list them all. Each type of music, like rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk, has created many smaller groups within itself.

Heavy Metal rock music has become one of the most interesting types of popular music in the past forty years. It shows many different feelings, usually dark ones. Soon after Heavy Metal began, musicians found they could change it in many ways. They made new kinds of Heavy Metal music. This process continues today.

Now there are so many different kinds of Heavy Metal that it is hard to say exactly what it is. It has taken ideas from many other types of music. To understand Heavy Metal music today, we need to know how it started and why it became more than just another kind of music.

Heavy Metal is often about dark things. It uses more of everything - more loud sounds, more strong feelings, and more dramatic shows. Heavy Metal musicians are very skilled at playing their instruments. In the middle of the 1970s, many musicians used drugs, which led them to make strange and unusual music. Heavy Metal was different from other popular music because it showed the darker side of life. Some of these dark ideas came from music written hundreds of years ago.

The song "Helter Skelter" by the Beatles was one of the first Heavy Metal songs. The Beatles wrote it to show they could make strong, dark music like the Rolling Stones. They put this song on their White Album.

Many years before artists began making strange dream-like pictures, Henri Rousseau was making his own special art. His famous painting from 1910, called "The Dream," shows a woman looking with wonder at the land she sees in her sleep. The painting also shows what Rousseau himself wanted - to be accepted and praised by other artists.

Rousseau was born in 1844 in a small French town called Laval. His father sold metal goods and had enough money to live well. Rousseau never went to art school. Instead, he worked for the French government collecting money from people at city gates until he was forty years old. His life was hard - his first wife died, and he lost eight babies, leaving him with just one daughter named Julia. He turned to painting to help him feel better and start a new life.

Unlike other artists of his time who painted pictures of poor people in a pretty way, Rousseau painted like someone who had learned on his own. He wanted very much to be accepted by other artists. This was hard because he started painting when he was older and had no training. At the same time, there were many well-known artists working, like Matisse. While Matisse tried to paint in new and different ways, Rousseau just wanted to paint pictures that would make other artists accept him.

Rousseau kept working even though many people did not understand his art at first. He painted what he saw in his mind - strange forests, animals, and dream worlds. His work was different from other artists, and this made it special, even though it took many years for people to see this.

Many wise people have seen a close link between what is good and what is beautiful. I believe there is a deep reason for this connection. The poet John Keats wrote that beauty and truth are the same thing, and this is all we need to know.

We learn many things in school and through life experiences. However, we seem to understand what is good and beautiful naturally, without being taught. When we study good behavior or beautiful art, we try to explain why they are special, rather than make rules about them.

When we talk about art or good behavior, we can never fully explain why they move us. For example, when people discuss the famous painting Mona Lisa, they might talk about colors or history. But these words alone cannot tell us why it is great art. Often, when someone talks about their favorite art, they first say "There is just something about it" before they give other reasons.

I believe both art and good behavior have qualities that cannot be completely described in words. The writer Flannery O'Connor said that sometimes a story is needed because simple words are not enough. Even when we describe all parts of a book or painting, something special remains unexplained. The same is true for good behavior.

I think art and good behavior are closely connected because we feel them deeply in our hearts, even when we cannot fully explain them. This is especially true with books and stories. Books are special because they show us how to live better lives. When we read, we think about what is right and wrong, just as we do in real life.

Germany today is a strong and united nation. Its culture spreads from the mountains in the south to the northern seas. You can feel this same culture as you travel from the western city of Cologne to the eastern city of Dresden. Germany's culture comes from many different groups of people who lived there long ago.

The old name for Germany was Germania. No one knows exactly where this name came from. Some say it came from an old group called the Tungrians. Others think it came from words meaning "neighbor" or "spear." Julius Caesar wrote about Germania when he fought wars there about two thousand years ago. He wrote that the people there often fought with their neighbors.

A man named Tacitus wrote about early Germans in the year 98. He believed they were the first people to live in that land. He wrote that the land was wild and cold, and wondered why anyone would want to move there unless it was already their home.

The Romans, who had a great empire to the south, did not want to live in Germania. They went there to trade and sometimes to fight, but they usually went back home. The German people lived near the edge of the Roman Empire. They sold things they made and grew, and some joined the Roman army to earn money.

The story "Twelfth Night" shows us how hiding who you are can help you trick others for a while, but in the end, you must return to being yourself. If you do not, you might lose your true self. However, when you stop pretending, people might turn away from you. You must then choose between staying true to yourself or keeping your friends. Some people might not mind finding out they were tricked, but others might become very angry.

When someone pretends to be the opposite sex, it raises many questions. The main question is why they do it. In the story, Viola arrives in a new place and decides to dress as a man to stay safe. This works, but it keeps her from making friends with other women who could help her. Things get harder when Olivia thinks Viola is a man and falls in love with her, mixing her up with her brother Sebastian. Also, Viola must hide her feelings for Orsino while pretending to be his male servant.

Today's readers might see how pretending to be someone else can bring hidden feelings to light, especially for Olivia and Orsino. We might wonder if Olivia loves Viola because she looks like a man, or if Olivia might have hidden feelings for women. But this is probably not what the writer wanted to show. Instead, the story makes fun of people who only care about how others look.

We can see this when Olivia quickly changes her love from Viola (dressed as Cesario) to Sebastian. At the end, she accepts Viola as family instead of a love interest, calling her "sister." This shows that the pretending helped everyone find their true feelings, even though it caused problems along the way.

The German control of other lands was often very cruel. This was especially true in South West Africa, where they killed many local Ovaherero and Nama people. However, we cannot say all German-controlled areas were the same. Different places were run in different ways.

Learning was also different across these areas. When the British took control of German East Africa in 1919, they found many African people who could read and write. In places like Kamerun, other writers also said good things about German teaching efforts.

But South West Africa (now called Namibia) was very different. In East Africa, the government made schools and helped teach local people. In South West Africa, they left teaching of local people mostly to church groups, giving them little help. However, the government spent much money to teach European people there. They made government schools and gave more help to church schools for Europeans.

These choices about schools had long-lasting effects. While other German-controlled areas had many African people who could read and write, in South West Africa most local people remained unable to read. Many things led to this different result in South West Africa. This study looks at these reasons, especially new findings about what settlers and government officials thought about African people.

Many people have written about schools in German-controlled lands. Most early writing was in German, from the time when Germany controlled these areas. These first works mostly just told how the schools worked. Later, English writers compared schools in different areas. They showed how different the schools were in each place. Cohen wrote the most important work about this topic, looking at schools in South West Africa and East Africa. He found that the large number of European settlers in South West Africa helped explain why schools there were different.

South West Africa had weather that Europeans could live in better than other German-controlled areas, even though much of it was dry desert. By 1913, almost 15,000 white people lived there. The next highest number was in East Africa, with only 5,336 white people.

The United States and Mexico were not friendly nations for many years, from 1836 to 1893. The biggest fight between them was the Mexican-American War from 1846 to 1848. In this war, the United States beat Mexico and took Texas and other land in the southwest. The two countries had many other smaller fights until just before World War One. These problems started because Americans and Mexicans were different in their beliefs, ways of life, and what they wanted.

This kind of problem is common between countries that share land borders. The United States and Mexico are like many other neighbors who do not get along. Writer David M. Pletcher says that among countries in the Americas, only Mexico and Cuba had long-lasting problems with the United States. Both these countries are close to the United States, while other countries in Latin America have better relations.

Religion was a big reason for the problems. Writer Sally Frahm says that in the 1700s and 1800s, Americans did not like Catholic religion and kings, just as they later did not like communism. Like the later fight with the Soviet Union, the problem with Mexico was partly about different beliefs and partly about what each country wanted. The Americans and Mexicans got these bad feelings from England and Spain, who ruled them before they became free countries.

Writers Diehl and Goerts found 17 fights between Mexico and the United States during these 57 years. Most of these fights were about bad people crossing the border and causing trouble. Both countries had to use their armies to stop these problems.

Writer Schmitt says the fighting began to stop when Mexico started to need the United States for help. By the end of the 1800s, the United States stopped wanting Mexican land and instead wanted to do business with Mexico.

Fifteen years ago, I got very sick with an illness I had never heard of before. This sickness left me unable to work.

I was a nurse then. I picked this job because I wanted to feel safe and secure, which I did not feel as a child. People told me, "You will always find work because people will always be sick." Even though I wanted to be a scientist or writer, I became a nurse instead.

Then at age 46, I was alone and had very little money. I could not work anymore. Today, after fifteen years of getting help from the government, I own almost nothing. I live day by day, but it is hard. I feel unsafe and worry a lot. While nothing is sure anymore, I know one truth: I could not have lived through these years without help from my family and friends. When big problems come, you do not feel strong at all.

Life will always have problems, big and small. We cannot plan for everything, and some problems are too big to face alone.

I think the United States should not depend only on the government, which is not working well. Instead, Americans should learn to trust and help each other again, rather than try to face everything alone.

Some people talk about how Americans should be strong and independent. But what really helped our early settlers was working together and sharing what they had. The people who moved west in wagons did not make it by being alone.

It is good to be ready for problems. I keep emergency supplies like first aid items, water tablets, and food. I have lights, matches, and other useful things. If you can grow food or heat your home with wood, that is good too.

But most important: get to know the people who live near you.

Around 2,500 years ago, a prince was born who would later be known as Buddha. During his life, he left his wealthy life behind and found deep wisdom. His teachings created Buddhism, and the oldest form of Buddhism is called Theravada. The religion has changed much since Buddha's time. For example, in the country of Sri Lanka, where many follow Theravada Buddhism, people take part in a yearly water ceremony. Both religious teachers and regular people join this ceremony, even though Buddha never spoke about such events. These changes can be seen in both small traditions and the deep beliefs of the religion. The Buddhist community has had to change its beliefs over time because of different forces, both from inside and outside their group.

Let me explain some important words we will use. When we say "inside force," we mean changes that come from Buddhist people themselves. "Outside force" means changes that come from non-Buddhist people. Some forces try to hurt Buddhism - we call these "harmful." Other forces neither try to help nor hurt Buddhism - we call these "neutral." These forces might still affect Buddhism in some way.

It is important to understand the basic ideas of Theravada Buddhism. Buddhists believe in three special things: Buddha, his teachings, and the community of Buddhist teachers. The teachings are written in three main groups of books. These books tell people how to live, explain rules to follow, and share deep ideas about life. The deep ideas say there is no eternal soul, that life includes suffering, and that nothing lasts forever. Understanding these ideas helps people break free from being born again and again. When people gain this understanding, they can end bad feelings like wanting too much, hating others, and being confused.

The books also give rules for living. Regular people must follow five main rules: do not kill, do not lie, do not take what is not given, do not act badly in love matters, and do not use things that harm the mind. Buddhist teachers must follow many more rules. The most important teaching is about four main truths: first, that life includes suffering; second, that wanting things causes suffering; and third, that we can stop suffering.
